        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 2:18PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 217 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Hope to near Springhill. Movement was
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stamps, Rosston, Buckner, Bodcaw, Laughlin, Waterloo, McNeil, Falcon,
Smithland, Mount Vernon, Morris, Piney Grove, Ebenezer, Bluff City,
Village, Taylor, Willisville, Sutton, Walkerville, and Magnolia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for northwestern
Louisiana.</instruction>
